9 AS INTRODUCED
10 An Act relating to criminal procedure; amending 22
O.S. 2021, Section 461, which relates to bail taken
11 in another county; authorizing defendants to post
bond in another jurisdiction under certain
12 circumstances; and providing an effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 22 O.S. 2021, Section 461, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 461. A. If the defendant is brought before a
19 magistrate of another county for the purpose of giving bail, the
20 magistrate must proceed in respect thereto, in the same manner as if
21 the defendant had been brought before him the magistrate upon a
22 warrant of arrest, and the same proceedings may be had thereon.
23 B. If a defendant is confined in a county jail, municipal jail,
24 or a jail operated by a regional jail authority, and the defendant
HB1991 HFLR Page 1
